text: A Little Firearms-Arcana for John Wick fans who are wondering what his pistols-of-choice are:   For those interested John likes the same 9mm pistols I carry: Glock 26 (one of the best every day carry-EDC- guns ever made, and just a damn good firearm to carry, you really don't need bigger), but if you do, he goes the way of the Hk-P30L ($900-1200, $750-ish used), or the Glock 34 9mm, which is like a Glock 17 but just a smidge bigger and some of the slide is cut-out to cut down on weight. It's a fucking tac-driver, approx $550-750 depending what's on it. And of course what many consider to be the best out-of-the-box combat handgun ever, the Glock 19. Though John clearly prefers 5.5-6" barrels, sure you can tag a steel plate @ 80 yards with a Glock 19 or 26 if you're good enough, but a 34 or HK-P30L with the right loads and eye you are almost operating with a little rifle in your hand in terms of accuracy and speed.   Since I'm clearly an expert badass like John Wick, I carry the glock 19 most days and don't even own a 34, but I got a 26 so when I Watch John Wick I put in a snap cap and go "pew pew! pew pew!" and pretend im awesome.

text: You know what's totally unfair. On the weekend this comes out in the US, only Fifty Shits Dumber is being released in Australia. While I didn't LOVE John Wick as much as everyone else, I certainly enjoyed it and am really looking forward to Chapter 2 but for whatever reason there hasn't been any advertising for it, no cinema websites say when it's coming out in Australia and it hasn't been given a rating yet. I know most of the time action thrillers like this starring big names such as Keanu Reeves come out the same weekend as the US down under but the fact there are no details on when it's coming out over here and it's US release is just next week really confuses and kind of worries me. Lionsgate please give this an Aussie theatrical release. Don't just send it straight to DVD this is John Wick we're talking about! (sigh) Also everything I've just said applies to New Zealand too. text: movies awesome and pretty funny. But if i had to nitpick at something, its the hand to hand combat scenes, to me they felt a little redundant after a while. in terms of the fighting styles and stradegies. like john wick keeps doing the flip move where he tosses the person over his head and shoulders to the ground. and also when hes on his back, he rolls around in a circle, when you watch the movie youll notice he does this quite often.   Idk i just felt they couldve mixed the moves up some. but Other then that? the movie was awesome.   Although a bit unbelieveable at times, like him and common still able to walk, let alone still be fighting! (which their fight scenes reminded me of peter griffin and the chicken fighting all over the city and buring the place down, from family guy lmao!) but after both (common and wick) were rolling down the hard concrete flight of steps which probably wouldve killed or severly crippled most people regardless of size and shape their in. Knees, shins, fibulas, ribs, hips, head, fingers! lol all of that would be shot after rolling down those steps with the kind of ferocity they were rolling down with. lol  and also how wick got hit by a car and it didnt snap his leg in half? lol john wick 1's fight and gun scenes felt more believable and in 2 it feels a bit more fiction. text: Grr..OMG.. this movie was seriously one of the worst action movies I've ever seen.  It made me pretty angry in fact because it was crazy stupid in every scene.  I love action films like Die Hard, Boondock Saints, The Raid 1&2, Hardcore Henry, etc.  But this was even worse than WANTED.  It's like playing an action FPS game, but one that is so basic and shallow that is has absolutely NO stealth mechanics, enemies have crap AI and charge and attack you straight on with NO planning.  DOOM is smarter than this!  Cops don't exist in this insane world and the crazy honor system it has only seems to apply to people when they feel like it.  There's no order to anything, every human on the street seems to be some undercover operator  where even the bums are not really bums but just pretending to be.  (If everyone is pretending to be something they are not than soon nobody would ever believe anyone was what they pretended to be!  Defeating the purpose)   but again nobody understands stealth so Sniper Rifles must not even exist.  Assassins just walk freely in the open showing no real skiills other than that of a drunken frat boy with an urge to take a swing at anything that moves.  Geez the force  of dumb just went on and on throughout this film that it so amazingly overhyped with great reviews.  I don't get it.  It just pisses me off that so many other better films go unnoticed while this crap get's stellar reviews.  This style of Gun Fu was done 15 yrs ago so much better in a little film called Equilibrium.
